objects.name: busy buzzard
objects.description: Busy Buzzard is a plugin-based Windows remote access tool. It is deployed as an RC4-encrypted Windows DLL, with a shellcode stub to decrypt and load it into memory.

objects.name: VMware
objects.description: VMware is a virtualization software company. Busy Buzzard checks for the presence of VMware to evade detection.

objects.name: Trend Micro
objects.description: Trend Micro is a cybersecurity company. They have identified a newer version of the Busy Buzzard TCP variant.

objects.name: PwC
objects.description: PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) is a professional services company. They have attributed a similar User-Agent string to the ChChes malware family.

objects.name: T1129
objects.description: Busy Buzzard uses the LoadLibraryW and GetProcAddress API functions to load additional modules and execute functions from them.

objects.name: T1106
objects.description: Busy Buzzard uses the VirtualAlloc and CreateThread API functions to inject and execute shellcode plugins.

objects.name: T1055.009
objects.description: Busy Buzzard is injected into the memory of a process, with additional shellcode modules also injected into the memory of the same process.

objects.name: T1497.001
objects.description: Busy Buzzard tests the Windows Registry for the presence of a key associated with VMware.

objects.name: T1083
objects.description: The Busy Buzzard shellcode plugin provides the capability to browse files and directories.

objects.name: T1082
objects.description: The Busy Buzzard beacon contains OS, username, hostname and process information.

objects.name: T1016
objects.description: The Busy Buzzard beacon contains the victim IP address.

objects.name: T1124
objects.description: The Busy Buzzard beacon contains the time at which the implant was started.

objects.name: T1071.001
objects.description: Busy Buzzard (HTTPS variant) uses HTTPS protocol for C2 communication.

objects.name: T1095
objects.description: Busy Buzzard (TCP variant) uses raw TCP protocol for C2 communication.

objects.name: T1573
objects.description: The Busy Buzzard beacon is RSA-encrypted using a hard-coded public key. Other C2 communications are RC4-encrypted using a shared, randomly generated, key.

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_command_switching_and_ok_response
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_command_switching_and_ok_response { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects code bytes used by Busy Buzzard to switch between the different commands, as well as a test for an 'ok' response from the C2 server" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" hash3 = "d2b8f4fe6eedb8b87521772fc823da596f2403b7" hash4 = "6a673508d46c0bbff74ee24384c8bc841c11ea4d" hash5 = "e74affd6c766156e3fe803917f28da08fe7000ef" hash6 = "48152eeb1d74a84ba86b34f419cf1c7a105e41ff" strings: $tcp   = {3C 64 74 ?? 3C 66 74 ?? 3C 6C 74 ?? 3C 73 75 ?? 8D 57 FB 48 8D 4B 05 E8} $http1 = {3C 64 74 ?? 3C 73} $http2 = {80 3B 6F 75 ?? 80 7B 01 6B 74} condition: $tcp or (all of ($http*)) }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_convert_crc32_to_mutex_name
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_convert_crc32_to_mutex_name { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects code bytes used by the TCP variant of Busy Buzzard to convert a CRC32 value to its hex string representation in reverse-nibble order" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" hash3 = "d2b8f4fe6eedb8b87521772fc823da596f2403b7" strings: $ = {0F B6 C2 24 0F 3C 09 76 02 04 07 04 30 48 FF C1 C1 EA 04 49 FF C8 88 41 FF 75 E5} condition: all of them }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_original_dll_names
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_original_dll_names { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects Busy Buzzard original DLL names embedded within the binary" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" hash3 = "6a673508d46c0bbff74ee24384c8bc841c11ea4d" hash4 = "e74affd6c766156e3fe803917f28da08fe7000ef" hash5 = "48152eeb1d74a84ba86b34f419cf1c7a105e41ff" strings: $ = "httpsWin32.dll\x00" $ = "tcpcX64.dll\x00" condition: any of them }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_random_rc4_key_generator
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_random_rc4_key_generator { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects code bytes used by Busy Buzzard to generate the randomised RC4 key" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" hash3 = "d2b8f4fe6eedb8b87521772fc823da596f2403b7" hash4 = "6a673508d46c0bbff74ee24384c8bc841c11ea4d" hash5 = "e74affd6c766156e3fe803917f28da08fe7000ef" hash6 = "48152eeb1d74a84ba86b34f419cf1c7a105e41ff" strings: $ = {99 B9 3E 00 00 00 F7 F9 83 FA 0A 73 05 83 C2 30 EB 0D 83 FA 25 73 05 83 C2 37 EB 03 83 C2 3C 8B 03 88 14 06 46 3B F7} $ = {44 8B D8 B8 43 08 21 84 41 F7 EB 41 03 D3 C1 FA 05 8B CA C1 E9 1F 03 D1 6B D2 3E 44 2B DA 41 83 FB 0A 7D 06 41 83 C3 30 EB 10 41 83 FB 25 7D 06 41 83 C3 37 EB 04 41 83 C3 3C 48 8B 4D 00 48 FF C3 48 FF CE 44 88 5C 0B FF 75 B0} condition: any of them }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_https_cmd_response_stack_strings
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_https_cmd_response_stack_strings { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects command response strings, built on the stack, used by the HTTPS variant of Busy Buzzard" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "6a673508d46c0bbff74ee24384c8bc841c11ea4d" hash2 = "e74affd6c766156e3fe803917f28da08fe7000ef" hash3 = "48152eeb1d74a84ba86b34f419cf1c7a105e41ff" strings: $ = {C7 (45 ?? | 85 ?? ?? ?? ??) 63 6D 64 3D} $ = {C7 (45 ?? | 85 ?? ?? ?? ??) 26 74 79 70 66 C7 (45 ?? | 85 ?? ?? ?? ??) 65 3D} $ = {C7 (45 ?? | 85 ?? ?? ?? ??) 26 72 65 74 66 C7 (45 ?? | 85 ?? ?? ?? ??) 3D 00} condition: all of them }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_plugin_helper_functions
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_plugin_helper_functions { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects code bytes used by Busy Buzzard shellcode plugin helper functions" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "f737067d41bc77dc7dd09ecb6eb710619bc2dfde" hash2 = "cf6339501de54590f8bbbc3cfb8051b95f6a1a42" strings: $ = {56 48 8B F4 48 83 E4 F0 48 83 EC 20 E8 F7 DF FF FF 48 8B E6 5E C3 48 C7 C0 30 00 00 00 65 48 8B 00 48 8B 40 60 48 8B 40 18 48 8B 40 10 48 8B 00 48 8B 00 48 8B 40 30 C3} condition: (all of them) and (filesize < 20KB) }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_shellcode_loader_x64
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_shellcode_loader_x64 { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects code bytes used for resolving function addresses in the Busy Buzzard shellcode loader" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" strings: $ = {3D 67 65 74 70} $ = {3D 64 64 72 65} $ = {C7 45 50 49 73 42 61} $ = {C7 45 54 64 52 65 61} $ = {C7 45 58 64 50 74 72} $ = {C7 45 20 49 6D 61 67} $ = {C7 45 24 65 52 76 61} $ = {C7 45 28 54 6F 56 61} $ = {48 C7 C0 30 00 00 00 65 48 8B 00 48 8B 40 60 48 8B 40 18 48 8B 40 10 48 8B 00 48 8B 00 48 8B 40 30 C3} condition: all of them }

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_rsa_public_keys

objects.name: BusyBuzzard_mutex_random_bytes
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule BusyBuzzard_mutex_random_bytes { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects additional random bytes used by TCP variants of Busy Buzzard to generate a unique mutex name" date = "2022-03-25" hash1 = "8fd99d9066020003358aa3e23c9af3d4911ce979" hash2 = "266852db4ad2d293469515820fd5e7c228cd4b3e" hash3 = "d2b8f4fe6eedb8b87521772fc823da596f2403b7" strings: $rand1 = {61 87 67 6C 6A DB 4A C6 58 D1 61} $rand2 = {CF 4F 26 6A 57 77 5B B7 AB D4 29} condition: (1 of ($rand*)) }
